    "95967750": {
      "title": "Application of 2-point Padé approximants to the ground state of the 2-dimensional hydrogen atom in an external magnetic field",
      "abstract": "The 2-dimensional hydrogen atom in an external field λr2 is important in certain problems of solid-state physics. The exact results for the ground state are obtained from the numerical solution of the radial Schrodinger equation and are compared with various 2-point Pade approximants. Terms to order λ4 in the low-field RS expansion are combined with 5 terms in the high-field expansion in order to obtain the Pade approximants. The results indicate that the best approximants have relative errors in the range 10−8 to 10−5 throughout the interval λ = 0 ⋯ 4."
    }
  },
